If you read the document about `ResourcesFromCode`, you will find

if you use **@...**, that means [a syntax to reference a resource in an XML resource](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/resources/providing-resources#fromXmlSyntax):

    @[&lt;package_name&gt;:]&lt;resource_type&gt;/&lt;resource_name&gt;

And if you use **?...**, that means you are [referencing a style attribute and the resource type portion is optional](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/resources/providing-resources#ReferencesToThemeAttributes):

    ?[&lt;package_name&gt;:][&lt;resource_type&gt;/]&lt;resource_name&gt;

You can get more examples and detailed information in the [document](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/resources/providing-resources#ResourcesFromCode).

And here is a link that may help: [question-mark-in-xml-attributes-for-android](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2733907/question-mark-in-xml-attributes-for-android)

